<http://dx.doi.org/10.5091/plecevo.96359.figure4>
    dc:description "Figure 4. Distribution maps of Podostemaceae in Gabon. A. Inversodicraea annithomae (grey circles), I. boumiensis (red diamonds). B. Inversodicraea nicolasii (red diamonds), I. paulsitae (grey circles), I. tenax (orange triangles). C. Inversodicraea thollonii (red diamonds), Ledermanniella bifurcata (grey circles). D. Ledermanniella aloides (grey circles), L. schlechteri (red diamonds)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/816314" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5091/plecevo.96359.figure8>
    dc:description "Figure 8. Photographs illustrating a selection of species treated in this paper. A, B, C. Ledermanniella schlechteri (A: Texier et al. 2335; B: Texier et al. 2274; C: Texier et al. 2250). D, E. Ledermanniella tenuifolia (D: Boupoya et al. 2417; E: Boupoya et al. 2426). F, G. Macropodiella hallaei (Texier et al. 2249). H, I. Saxicolella nana (Boupoya et al. 1952). Photographs: Nicolas Texier (A-C, F, G), Archange Boupoya (D, E, H, I)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/816318" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

